  // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  // LAIRS / NESTS (ENTITIES_SPAWNING territory) — `lair: true` — listed FIRST (same reason as the
  // groves above): Pass-1 scatter is first-match-wins, so a lair listed AFTER the common
  // trees/grass (grass_patch alone claims 92% of grass tiles) almost never gets rolled — that
  // starved them (swamp_nest → 0). Listed first, each lair type gets a fair, independent shot.
  // Probabilities are therefore TINY (no longer suppressed) — a den is a rare landmark, the SOLE
  // source of laired hostiles. Each placed tile seeds ONE bound pack of a creature whose `lair`
  // (creatures.jsonc) matches its id; the pack stays leashed within `lairRange`.
  // Destructible: the DESTROY button marks it for the "harvest" path, which consumes the
  // (non-persistent) node and razes the den (stopping its repopulation/growth).
  // TODO: drop loot on destroy — a cleared den should reward the player (hoarded bones/goods, a
  // trophy, a rare material).
  {
